verbose_text: Although two thirds of participants in the high DED group were randomized to the low BP arm compared to approximately one third of the low DED subjects, BP levels during the trial were only slightly lower (by 2 mmHg for SBP and 3 mmHg for DBP) in the high DED group, indicating that high DED participants did not always achieve their BP goal despite higher RAAS blocking drug doses and more frequent use of diuretics.
